# Current State Pointers

Before starting work, check (don't assume — these change often):

- **What's active right now:** `.playbook/19_CURRENT_SPRINT.md`
- **What's next, in what order:** `.playbook/14_ROADMAP.md` (active milestone only; completed milestones'
  full detail is in `.playbook/25_ROADMAP_ARCHIVE.md`)
- **Full project overview, constitution, and living-state memory:** `.playbook/00_PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md`
- **Why something was decided:** `.playbook/12_DECISIONS.md`
- **What changed, and when:** `.playbook/13_CHANGELOG.md`

Every other `.playbook/` document (coding standard, style guide, data model, company schema, accessibility,
security, performance, etc.) is topic-specific reference material — read it when the task actually touches that
topic, not by default. Several are also auto-attached via other rules in this directory based on which files you're
editing.
